1
00:00:06,354 --> 00:00:08,442
[SUZUKI] Thanks to our
super romantical class trip...

2
00:00:08,442 --> 00:00:08,753
[SUZUKI] Thanks to our
super romantical class trip...

3
00:00:08,753 --> 00:00:11,531
[gasps] Oh, Tani!

4
00:00:12,248 --> 00:00:14,899
...Tani and I are closer
than we've ever been before.

5
00:00:14,899 --> 00:00:16,498
Hola!

6
00:00:16,708 --> 00:00:18,308
You recharge your batteries
after the trip?

7
00:00:18,519 --> 00:00:19,519
Yeah.

8
00:00:19,660 --> 00:00:20,660
How are you, Suzuki?

9
00:00:20,660 --> 00:00:23,784
[SUZUKI] Just kidding,
things are the same as always.

10
00:00:24,320 --> 00:00:26,460
Huh? What is it?
Is something wrong?

11
00:00:26,710 --> 00:00:29,123
[muttering]
Still plain ol' "Suzuki."

12
00:00:29,123 --> 00:00:31,335
OH.

13
00:00:32,040 --> 00:00:33,040
Miyu.

14
00:00:33,798 --> 00:00:35,088
[groans nervously]

15
00:00:36,415 --> 00:00:38,502
Wait a second,
but you just called me Tani

16
00:00:38,691 --> 00:00:39,691
instead of Yuusuke.

17
00:00:39,754 --> 00:00:41,347
[SUZUKI]
Really? I didn't notice.

18
00:00:41,840 --> 00:00:44,439
Then again, we are at school,

19
00:00:44,439 --> 00:00:46,620
so gotta keep things
a little profesh.

20
00:00:46,825 --> 00:00:48,102
[TANI] Yeah, you're right.

21
00:00:48,925 --> 00:00:51,189
Wait, so you wouldn't
be profesh if we were,

22
00:00:51,394 --> 00:00:52,836
you know, alone?

23
00:00:52,836 --> 00:00:55,387
You know, are you saying
that if the mood was just right,

24
00:00:55,393 --> 00:00:56,393
you'd, you know...

25
00:00:56,499 --> 00:00:59,092
No, I really don't think I do.

26
00:00:59,092 --> 00:01:00,656
[SUZUKI] To ze common eye,

27
00:01:00,862 --> 00:01:03,496
this romance has made
few large developments.

28
00:01:03,703 --> 00:01:06,460
But the improvements
are incremental.

29
00:01:06,666 --> 00:01:08,272
Who are you talking to?

30
00:01:09,094 --> 00:01:12,799
I'm just out here chroniclin'
the small imperfections o' life.

31
00:01:12,799 --> 00:01:14,651
It's called wabi-sabi.

32
00:01:14,857 --> 00:01:16,339
Satou, your handwriting.

33
00:01:16,545 --> 00:01:17,862
Pretty, right?

34
00:01:17,862 --> 00:01:19,302
How come you're the one
acting proud?

35
00:01:19,509 --> 00:01:21,979
[laughing]

36
00:01:22,184 --> 00:01:23,377
Yeah, wait a sec.

37
00:01:23,789 --> 00:01:24,901
I MIGHT
JUST BE IMAGINING IT, BUT.

38
00:01:24,901 --> 00:01:26,012
[SUZUKI] Am I crazy,
or did Azuma

39
00:01:26,218 --> 00:01:27,576
totally shake her storm cloud?

40
00:01:27,783 --> 00:01:29,181
Where's her negative aura?

41
00:01:29,470 --> 00:01:30,952
AFTER SCHOOL

42
00:01:30,952 --> 00:01:32,392
Hey, Tani, did you already
order some class trip pics?

43
00:01:32,599 --> 00:01:33,599
Not yet.

44
00:01:33,599 --> 00:01:36,072
[SUZUKI]
Tani's social circle is growing.

45
00:01:36,282 --> 00:01:37,707
It's like whenever
I take my eyes off him,

46
00:01:37,917 --> 00:01:39,006
he's made a new friend.

47
00:01:39,006 --> 00:01:40,432
You at least
have to order this one.

48
00:01:40,432 --> 00:01:41,983
You're moggin' us all.

49
00:01:41,983 --> 00:01:43,995
I don't know what that means,
but it sounds like a lie.

50
00:01:43,995 --> 00:01:45,294
THEY WERE IN THE BIG ROOM
WITH HIM

51
00:01:45,504 --> 00:01:46,845
STARE

52
00:01:46,845 --> 00:01:48,480
[Saotome gasps]
Suzuki's staring into my soul!

53
00:01:48,689 --> 00:01:51,163
Show me my man's glamour shots,
or else.

54
00:01:51,666 --> 00:01:54,642
[laughs] What the heck's
going on here?

55
00:01:54,642 --> 00:01:57,535
Some guy walked in and we
asked him to take a pic for us.

56
00:01:57,744 --> 00:01:59,253
[laughs]

57
00:01:59,463 --> 00:02:00,847
-And here's the hot one.
-[Suzuki laughs]

58
00:02:01,056 --> 00:02:02,565
This is so dumb!

59
00:02:02,859 --> 00:02:05,415
Aww, if you won't order these,
I totally will.

60
00:02:05,626 --> 00:02:07,135
[TANI] You should
save your money.

61
00:02:08,308 --> 00:02:11,871
[grumbles] There are so many
to choose from.

62
00:02:11,871 --> 00:02:13,423
You should just
pick out a few faves.

63
00:02:13,632 --> 00:02:15,435
These prices are
highway robbery.

64
00:02:15,644 --> 00:02:17,362
This reminds me
of when Gapacho ordered

65
00:02:17,362 --> 00:02:19,165
a bunch of photos
from our middle-school trip,

66
00:02:19,374 --> 00:02:21,052
and not a single one of them
had him in it.

67
00:02:21,261 --> 00:02:23,776
Apparently his folks were
super pissed off about it.

68
00:02:23,986 --> 00:02:25,411
[SUZUKI]
So he just got the landscapes?

69
00:02:25,621 --> 00:02:26,711
Gapacho's an artiste!

70
00:02:26,920 --> 00:02:27,968
[TAIRA] I'd do the same.

71
00:02:27,968 --> 00:02:29,226
HE DOESN'T WANT
PHOTOS OF HIMSELF

72
00:02:29,435 --> 00:02:30,435
HE WANTS A RECORD OF THE TRIP.

73
00:02:30,441 --> 00:02:31,615
Boom, bought 'em.

74
00:02:31,615 --> 00:02:33,879
I'm not in too many,
so that was easy.

75
00:02:33,879 --> 00:02:36,017
What? There's a lot of you. See?

76
00:02:36,226 --> 00:02:39,496
[exclaims] You know better than
to fall for deepfakes, girl!

77
00:02:39,706 --> 00:02:40,921
[Honda sighs]

78
00:02:40,921 --> 00:02:42,933
Finally, a day
where I'm not bogged down

79
00:02:43,143 --> 00:02:44,611
by student council work.

80
00:02:44,611 --> 00:02:46,790
Ever since our classmates
picked me to be class rep

81
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:48,970
while I was out sick,
I've hated their guts.

82
00:02:48,970 --> 00:02:52,030
That being said, don't you think
the class trip was super sweet?

83
00:02:52,240 --> 00:02:53,414
[Nishi gasps]

84
00:02:53,414 --> 00:02:55,174
Uh, yeah, it was nice.

85
00:02:55,970 --> 00:02:57,438
[students chattering]

86
00:02:57,438 --> 00:02:58,444
Mm?

87
00:02:58,862 --> 00:02:59,911
[Nishi gasps]

88
00:03:03,012 --> 00:03:04,061
[AZUMA] No, don't.
I like that one.

89
00:03:04,270 --> 00:03:05,361
[whimpers]

90
00:03:05,612 --> 00:03:06,744
[gasps]

91
00:03:08,253 --> 00:03:10,810
So, have you two
set up your date?

92
00:03:10,810 --> 00:03:11,810
[NISHI] What?

93
00:03:13,369 --> 00:03:14,369
Oh, well, um...

94
00:03:15,522 --> 00:03:17,665
[♪ opening theme song playing]

95
00:03:27,100 --> 00:03:31,880
YOU AND I ARE POLAR OPPOSITES

96
00:04:46,579 --> 00:04:47,579
[NISHI] What do I do?

97
00:04:48,152 --> 00:04:49,709
Wanna hang out later?

98
00:04:49,915 --> 00:04:51,145
After the class trip?

99
00:04:52,456 --> 00:04:54,465
[NISHI] It's out
of character for me,

100
00:04:54,793 --> 00:04:56,473
but maybe just this once,

101
00:04:56,842 --> 00:04:58,523
I'll try to dress up.

102
00:04:59,547 --> 00:05:01,352
The last time I dressed fancy...

103
00:05:01,556 --> 00:05:04,589
Oh my. Well, don't you look
like a cute little cupcake.

104
00:05:04,589 --> 00:05:05,902
[NISHI]
Ever since Mom said that,

105
00:05:05,902 --> 00:05:08,197
I've been embarrassed
to wear this stuff!

106
00:05:08,566 --> 00:05:10,615
I've barely
ever worn this dress.

107
00:05:10,821 --> 00:05:12,051
Should I wear it now?

108
00:05:12,420 --> 00:05:14,039
Will it be okay?

109
00:05:14,039 --> 00:05:16,678
Or is it too weird
for a casual meet up?

110
00:05:16,890 --> 00:05:19,656
I'm usually a function-
over-fashion kind of girl.

111
00:05:19,870 --> 00:05:21,827
You should always wear
what you want to.

112
00:05:22,040 --> 00:05:23,402
It doesn't matter
what people think.

113
00:05:23,402 --> 00:05:25,870
If you wanna be a cupcake,
lay on the frosting.

114
00:05:26,594 --> 00:05:28,935
[NISHI] All right,
fancy dress it is!

115
00:05:29,359 --> 00:05:30,977
This is my chance.

116
00:05:30,977 --> 00:05:33,616
I've bought lots of random
accessories over the years,

117
00:05:33,828 --> 00:05:35,658
but I've never
actually worn them.

118
00:05:39,149 --> 00:05:40,149
Huh?

119
00:05:41,629 --> 00:05:42,629
What's going on?

120
00:05:44,288 --> 00:05:45,946
What is this feeling?

121
00:05:46,339 --> 00:05:47,699
My heart is racing,

122
00:05:47,699 --> 00:05:50,239
and it just won't stop!

123
00:05:52,738 --> 00:05:54,279
-[birds chirping]
-[door opens]

124
00:05:54,279 --> 00:05:55,404
I'm heading out.

125
00:05:55,612 --> 00:05:57,236
[NISHI'S MOM] What? This early?

126
00:05:57,985 --> 00:05:59,402
[NISHI] That was close.

127
00:05:59,610 --> 00:06:01,150
I managed to leave
without my family seeing me!

128
00:06:01,372 --> 00:06:02,613
ALL DECKED OUT
WHEW.

129
00:06:02,969 --> 00:06:05,453
I'm probably
realizing a little late,

130
00:06:05,764 --> 00:06:09,224
but nothing in my outfit
actually goes well together.

131
00:06:09,445 --> 00:06:11,841
I bought each item
because it was cute on its own

132
00:06:12,062 --> 00:06:13,881
and didn't even think
about coordinating it

133
00:06:14,103 --> 00:06:15,788
with the rest of my wardrobe.

134
00:06:16,187 --> 00:06:18,628
[indistinct chatter]

135
00:06:19,115 --> 00:06:20,313
[NISHI] It's funny.

136
00:06:20,535 --> 00:06:21,822
THE STATION
WHERE THEY'RE MEETING

137
00:06:21,822 --> 00:06:24,084
I never really
noticed it before today,

138
00:06:24,528 --> 00:06:26,258
but all the girls
walking down the street

139
00:06:26,479 --> 00:06:28,209
look so fashionable!

140
00:06:28,431 --> 00:06:29,431
SHOWY
SHOWY

141
00:06:29,628 --> 00:06:31,403
I gotta take these off!

142
00:06:31,403 --> 00:06:32,601
-[cell phone buzzes]
-[gasps]

143
00:06:33,666 --> 00:06:36,327
I'M HERE!
WHERE ARE YOU RIGHT NOW?

144
00:06:36,860 --> 00:06:39,439
[NISHI]
Um, I'm already here too.

145
00:06:41,293 --> 00:06:48,293
I'm near the top
of the back escalator,

146
00:06:49,558 --> 00:06:55,544
over on the platform.

147
00:07:05,807 --> 00:07:11,653
[whimpering]

148
00:07:19,063 --> 00:07:23,483
[cell phone buzzing]

149
00:07:24,194 --> 00:07:29,897
NISHI-SAN
INCOMING CALL

150
00:07:31,180 --> 00:07:36,595
Yellow, Nishi.

151
00:07:36,595 --> 00:07:40,159
You good?

152
00:07:40,871 --> 00:07:44,152
Are you lost?

153
00:07:44,152 --> 00:07:51,152
[NISHI] No, I'm already here.

154
00:07:51,989 --> 00:07:57,120
Whoa, where at?

155
00:07:57,835 --> 00:08:04,835
[NISHI] Um, if you go up
the escalator, there's, uh,

156
00:08:09,093 --> 00:08:14,652
I suppose it's a plaza.

157
00:08:15,367 --> 00:08:19,784
[YAMADA] Hmm.

158
00:08:30,334 --> 00:08:36,748
She'll never see me like that.

159
00:08:39,597 --> 00:08:46,597
I'm standing
next to the ticket gates.

160
00:08:48,861 --> 00:08:52,569
-[YAMADA] Heya.
-What?

161
00:08:53,281 --> 00:08:57,701
Reception isn't so--

162
00:08:57,701 --> 00:09:02,261
[gasps] Forgive me, sir.

163
00:09:02,972 --> 00:09:08,959
-So formal.
-[squeals]

164
00:09:08,959 --> 00:09:13,235
And intense.

165
00:09:13,950 --> 00:09:20,950
Oh, I apologize.
I didn't realize it was you.

166
00:09:24,353 --> 00:09:31,339
[YAMADA] You sounded all shaky
on the phone, too.

167
00:09:31,339 --> 00:09:32,339
Sorry.

168
00:09:32,339 --> 00:09:33,097
Wait, are you nervous?

169
00:09:33,097 --> 00:09:33,870
[NISHI]
Are you really asking that?!

170
00:09:33,870 --> 00:09:34,919
[whimpers] Yeah, I am.

171
00:09:35,998 --> 00:09:36,998
-[YAMADA] Me too.
-[Nishi gasps]

172
00:09:38,044 --> 00:09:39,044
[NISHI] Wait, now that
I've got a closer look,

173
00:09:39,192 --> 00:09:40,402
did Yamada style his hair
a little differently than usual?

174
00:09:40,402 --> 00:09:41,402
Smooth as ice.

175
00:09:41,402 --> 00:09:42,108
[NISHI] Now I can't remember.

176
00:09:42,108 --> 00:09:42,939
What does it normally look like?

177
00:09:42,939 --> 00:09:43,939
Come to think of it,
I never look Yamada in the eye

178
00:09:43,939 --> 00:09:44,587
or even at his face
when we talk.

179
00:09:44,587 --> 00:09:45,587
SHE LOOKS AT THIS AREA

180
00:09:45,787 --> 00:09:46,614
CHINATOWN

181
00:09:46,614 --> 00:09:47,489
Going to a place
I've never been.

182
00:09:47,489 --> 00:09:48,481
Wearing something
besides my uniform.

183
00:09:48,481 --> 00:09:49,481
Walking together, just us two.

184
00:09:50,088 --> 00:09:50,755
It's hard to believe

185
00:09:50,755 --> 00:09:51,755
that we're even part
of each other's worlds.

186
00:09:51,765 --> 00:09:52,709
Of all the girls out there,

187
00:09:52,709 --> 00:09:53,511
how am I the one
walking next to him?

188
00:09:53,511 --> 00:09:54,124
-Wanna eat something?
-[gasps]

189
00:09:54,124 --> 00:09:54,634
I am kinda peckry.

190
00:09:54,634 --> 00:09:55,334
Wait, I mean hungry.

191
00:09:55,334 --> 00:09:56,311
You know,
I'm kinda peckry myself.

192
00:09:56,311 --> 00:09:57,055
[whimpers]

193
00:09:57,055 --> 00:09:57,521
[NISHI]
I was gonna say "peckish"

194
00:09:57,521 --> 00:09:58,221
and switched words
halfway through.

195
00:09:58,221 --> 00:09:58,688
That's normalry.

196
00:09:58,688 --> 00:09:59,067
[Nishi whimpering]

197
00:09:59,067 --> 00:10:00,067
Whoa, looks good.

198
00:10:00,067 --> 00:10:00,671
I should've
asked this earlier,

199
00:10:00,671 --> 00:10:01,414
but is it cool with you
that I chose the restaurant?

200
00:10:01,414 --> 00:10:01,823
Mm-hm.

201
00:10:01,823 --> 00:10:02,421
I've got no idea why,

202
00:10:02,421 --> 00:10:03,237
but I was like mega craving
a warm meat bun.

203
00:10:03,237 --> 00:10:03,777
Yeah, the weather did cool down.

204
00:10:03,777 --> 00:10:04,156
-It did.
-It's nice.

205
00:10:04,156 --> 00:10:04,549
AWARD WINNING XIAO LONG BAO
ULTIMATE

206
00:10:04,549 --> 00:10:04,929
[YAMADA]
I usually stop by Taira's work

207
00:10:04,929 --> 00:10:05,556
whenever I wanna get
some steamies,

208
00:10:05,556 --> 00:10:05,935
but then I caught a whiff

209
00:10:05,935 --> 00:10:06,489
of some
delicious-smelling meat buns

210
00:10:06,489 --> 00:10:06,941
on my way home the other day.

211
00:10:06,941 --> 00:10:07,941
And I thought, "I gotta
chow down in Chinatown."

212
00:10:07,941 --> 00:10:08,778
Oh, there's this new
convenience store I go to,

213
00:10:08,778 --> 00:10:09,303
that's where my boy Taira works.

214
00:10:09,303 --> 00:10:10,303
[NISHI] Taira,
the boy with brown hair.

215
00:10:10,303 --> 00:10:10,732
[YAMADA] It was hilarious.

216
00:10:10,732 --> 00:10:11,432
Mini had Morimo
dying of laughter.

217
00:10:11,432 --> 00:10:11,986
[NISHI] I'm learning
more and more names,

218
00:10:11,986 --> 00:10:12,832
thanks to Yamada's stories.

219
00:10:12,832 --> 00:10:13,328
[YAMADA]
So I went to ask Gapacho

220
00:10:13,328 --> 00:10:13,940
if he wanted to go when, uh...

221
00:10:13,940 --> 00:10:14,698
Oh, God, have I been
talking this whole time?

222
00:10:14,698 --> 00:10:15,296
-Your go.
-Oh!

223
00:10:15,296 --> 00:10:16,098
Uh...

224
00:10:16,098 --> 00:10:17,163
-Back in the line, you lost me.
-What?

225
00:10:17,163 --> 00:10:17,848
You used a strange word.

226
00:10:17,848 --> 00:10:18,373
I didn't know what
you were talking about

227
00:10:18,373 --> 00:10:18,869
when you said "steamies."

228
00:10:18,869 --> 00:10:19,802
It's what I call store-bought
meat and pizza buns.

229
00:10:19,802 --> 00:10:20,371
I see.

230
00:10:20,371 --> 00:10:20,677
STARE.

231
00:10:20,677 --> 00:10:21,114
What else were you lost on?

232
00:10:21,114 --> 00:10:21,931
You said you "caught a whiff
of meat buns."

233
00:10:21,931 --> 00:10:22,354
Curry would make sense,

234
00:10:22,354 --> 00:10:22,922
but meat buns don't
have a strong smell.

235
00:10:22,922 --> 00:10:23,535
Oh, come on, they totally do!

236
00:10:23,535 --> 00:10:23,987
You know, on the train,

237
00:10:23,987 --> 00:10:24,556
when someone's got
a takeout box full of 'em,

238
00:10:24,556 --> 00:10:24,920
it invades your brain.

239
00:10:24,920 --> 00:10:25,824
-It's like stank psyops!
-[laughs]

240
00:10:25,824 --> 00:10:26,553
-"Chow down in Chinatown."
-Whoa.

241
00:10:26,553 --> 00:10:27,209
Talk about a delayed reaction.

242
00:10:27,209 --> 00:10:28,055
I can't even remember
why I made that joke.

243
00:10:28,055 --> 00:10:28,595
How come you didn't laugh
when I said it?

244
00:10:28,595 --> 00:10:28,989
[NISHI] I'm sorry.

245
00:10:28,989 --> 00:10:29,586
It was funny,
but you were talking,

246
00:10:29,586 --> 00:10:30,374
and I didn't wanna
interrupt your story.

247
00:10:30,374 --> 00:10:30,913
Interrupt away, girl.

248
00:10:30,913 --> 00:10:31,380
Don't remind me
I made a cringe joke

249
00:10:31,380 --> 00:10:32,153
-way after the fact.
-[laughs]

250
00:10:32,153 --> 00:10:32,751
"It's like stank psyops."

251
00:10:32,751 --> 00:10:33,319
Now what did I just tell you?

252
00:10:33,319 --> 00:10:34,136
[laughs]

253
00:10:34,136 --> 00:10:34,734
What'd you end up doing
on the class trip

254
00:10:34,734 --> 00:10:35,113
in your free time?

255
00:10:35,113 --> 00:10:35,477
Um, well,

256
00:10:35,477 --> 00:10:36,265
-I went to a comedy show.
-Mm-hmm.

257
00:10:36,265 --> 00:10:37,023
And I took a lot
of scenic photos,

258
00:10:37,023 --> 00:10:37,679
and saw
the electronics district.

259
00:10:37,679 --> 00:10:38,190
[YAMADA] Sick.

260
00:10:38,190 --> 00:10:41,070
Most of my class just went
to Ultra Super Jumbo Land.

261
00:10:41,070 --> 00:10:42,965
[NISHI] The photo you sent me
of you guys

262
00:10:43,175 --> 00:10:44,902
in the puppy hats was so funny.

263
00:10:45,112 --> 00:10:46,712
[YAMADA] Yeah, but now
I can't wear it anymore.

264
00:10:46,924 --> 00:10:48,903
Can't recycle the fit.
It's too iconic.

265
00:10:49,113 --> 00:10:50,798
[both laughing]

266
00:10:51,008 --> 00:10:52,566
[NISHI] Just this morning,

267
00:10:52,566 --> 00:10:54,798
I was nervous about meeting
outside of school,

268
00:10:55,009 --> 00:10:57,115
but my anxiety's fading away.

269
00:10:57,451 --> 00:10:58,883
Spending the day with him,

270
00:10:59,094 --> 00:11:01,157
around nobody else
that I know,

271
00:11:01,368 --> 00:11:03,348
it's weirdly comfortable.

272
00:11:08,864 --> 00:11:11,517
It'd be nice
if he felt the same way.

273
00:11:12,750 --> 00:11:13,750
Hey. Come on, let's walk
over to that bridge.

274
00:11:13,750 --> 00:11:14,750
[♪ tender music playing]

275
00:11:14,785 --> 00:11:15,785
Whoa, check it.

276
00:11:19,444 --> 00:11:26,444
This place is so sick,
it makes the view extra pretty.

277
00:11:39,730 --> 00:11:40,730
[NISHI] What do I do?

278
00:11:40,984 --> 00:11:42,458
It's too much.

279
00:11:42,458 --> 00:11:44,288
I think my heart's
going to explode!

280
00:11:44,542 --> 00:11:45,915
CAN'T PAY ATTENTION
TO SCENERY RIGHT NOW

281
00:11:46,170 --> 00:11:47,170
I can't look at his face.

282
00:11:48,077 --> 00:11:54,803
[Yamada shivers]
Man, that's chilly.

283
00:11:56,439 --> 00:12:03,439
The ocean breeze
really hits ya.

284
00:12:04,435 --> 00:12:11,435
[NISHI]
Yamada's still acting normal.

285
00:12:13,526 --> 00:12:20,526
Am I the only one
who feels all giddy inside?

286
00:12:26,612 --> 00:12:33,612
Like my emotions
are going crazy?

287
00:12:39,515 --> 00:12:45,151
[gasps]

288
00:12:46,058 --> 00:12:50,604
[gasps]

289
00:12:52,419 --> 00:12:53,419
Huh?

290
00:12:53,419 --> 00:12:53,879
Over there.

291
00:12:53,879 --> 00:12:54,879
Hmm?

292
00:12:55,458 --> 00:12:56,458
[both gasp]

293
00:12:56,458 --> 00:12:57,366
[both exclaim]

294
00:12:57,366 --> 00:12:58,089
-[YAMADA] Abort!
-[NISHI] Yes, sir!

295
00:12:58,089 --> 00:12:58,563
[YAMADA] So fast! Wait!

296
00:12:58,563 --> 00:12:59,273
Nishi, your bag's open!

297
00:12:59,273 --> 00:13:00,273
-[panting]
-That was close.

298
00:13:00,455 --> 00:13:01,455
Yeesh, I would've preferred
a less chaotic ending,

299
00:13:01,455 --> 00:13:02,036
but that's life.

300
00:13:02,036 --> 00:13:02,997
[Nishi panting]
Sorry, my curfew's so early.

301
00:13:02,997 --> 00:13:03,707
Hey, don't worry. It's cool.

302
00:13:03,707 --> 00:13:04,457
You just focus on breathing.

303
00:13:04,457 --> 00:13:04,983
Oh, yeah.

304
00:13:04,983 --> 00:13:05,602
When we were making our getaway,

305
00:13:05,602 --> 00:13:06,115
you dropped all sorts of stuff.

306
00:13:06,115 --> 00:13:06,562
[Nishi gasps]

307
00:13:06,562 --> 00:13:07,154
[YAMADA] I don't think I've ever
seen you wear these.

308
00:13:07,154 --> 00:13:07,615
Do you usually
carry them around?

309
00:13:07,615 --> 00:13:08,273
Um, not really.

310
00:13:08,273 --> 00:13:08,957
Well, you should put
some of 'em on.

311
00:13:08,957 --> 00:13:09,536
-Huh?
-It'll look cute.

312
00:13:09,536 --> 00:13:09,970
[NISHI] Cute?

313
00:13:09,970 --> 00:13:10,575
[YAMADA] I like this fluffy one.

314
00:13:10,575 --> 00:13:11,338
[NISHI]
Oh, he means the clip is cute.

315
00:13:11,338 --> 00:13:11,904
-[exclaims]
-[YAMADA] Just a sec.

316
00:13:11,904 --> 00:13:12,312
This is tough.

317
00:13:12,312 --> 00:13:12,865
Girls have mad skills.

318
00:13:12,865 --> 00:13:13,654
Oops. Sorry, it looks weird.

319
00:13:13,654 --> 00:13:14,128
[NISHI] Mm.

320
00:13:14,128 --> 00:13:14,720
Then again,

321
00:13:14,720 --> 00:13:15,509
now you can look me
in the eye more.

322
00:13:15,509 --> 00:13:16,351
I noticed you don't do
very much of that.

323
00:13:16,351 --> 00:13:16,720
[NISHI] Unfortunately,

324
00:13:16,720 --> 00:13:18,259
that's not a problem
with my bangs.

325
00:13:19,600 --> 00:13:20,600
It's a problem with me.

326
00:13:21,303 --> 00:13:22,960
Yeah, I'm sorry.

327
00:13:24,467 --> 00:13:27,529
Okay, I'll start looking.

328
00:13:27,781 --> 00:13:29,337
Now!

329
00:13:29,337 --> 00:13:31,748
You say that,
but your eyes are still closed.

330
00:13:32,100 --> 00:13:33,120
From now on.

331
00:13:33,255 --> 00:13:34,255
Oh, how 'bout now?

332
00:13:35,799 --> 00:13:37,079
Let's hang out again.

333
00:13:37,399 --> 00:13:38,399
Just us.

334
00:13:40,434 --> 00:13:41,495
Mm.

335
00:13:48,705 --> 00:13:50,571
[both gasp]

336
00:13:51,631 --> 00:13:52,776
[both exclaim]

337
00:13:52,988 --> 00:13:53,988
[YAMADA] Abort!

338
00:13:54,346 --> 00:13:55,873
[tape rewinding]

339
00:13:59,732 --> 00:14:01,090
EXPLANATION

340
00:14:01,301 --> 00:14:03,337
While Yamada and Nishi
were about to get

341
00:14:03,549 --> 00:14:04,737
their snow on the road,

342
00:14:04,949 --> 00:14:05,949
that very same day,

343
00:14:05,973 --> 00:14:06,973
about an hour earlier.

344
00:14:07,889 --> 00:14:08,889
Wow!

345
00:14:10,029 --> 00:14:17,029
This rules!

346
00:14:22,362 --> 00:14:29,362
A blue sky,

347
00:14:31,500 --> 00:14:38,500
the fresh ocean air,

348
00:14:41,778 --> 00:14:48,778
and a popping place
for sightseeing.

349
00:14:54,112 --> 00:15:00,964
Is it just me,
or is this like...

350
00:15:03,705 --> 00:15:10,705
an extra date-y date?

351
00:15:17,179 --> 00:15:18,179
What do I do?

352
00:15:18,179 --> 00:15:19,730
My heart's already
pounding like crazy!

353
00:15:20,027 --> 00:15:22,138
On the class trip, we had
a couple of romantic momos,

354
00:15:22,304 --> 00:15:23,887
but most of the time,
we were busy hanging

355
00:15:24,052 --> 00:15:25,570
with-slash-near
the rest of the crew.

356
00:15:27,550 --> 00:15:28,738
GLOMP.

357
00:15:28,738 --> 00:15:31,047
This is my chance to indulge
and get supes snuggly!

358
00:15:31,212 --> 00:15:32,400
He won't mind, right?

359
00:15:32,565 --> 00:15:33,565
I know I won't!

360
00:15:33,588 --> 00:15:35,634
NO REACTION.

361
00:15:36,360 --> 00:15:38,405
Whatever!
Today, I don't give a flip!

362
00:15:38,570 --> 00:15:39,570
SNUGGLE.

363
00:15:39,857 --> 00:15:41,441
Because today is special.

364
00:15:41,606 --> 00:15:42,662
Hey, that looks delish!

365
00:15:42,826 --> 00:15:44,675
We're a ways away
from where we live.

366
00:15:44,839 --> 00:15:45,839
We're alone.

367
00:15:45,863 --> 00:15:47,479
I'm gonna need
like ten of those.

368
00:15:47,644 --> 00:15:48,700
Pick your poison, Yuusuke.

369
00:15:48,865 --> 00:15:51,208
I gotta enjoy this vacay
from everyday life.

370
00:15:51,373 --> 00:15:53,616
Peak choice!
I think I'm gonna get a...

371
00:15:53,782 --> 00:15:54,782
Wha...

372
00:15:56,419 --> 00:15:57,419
-[gasps]
-[TANI] Great.

373
00:15:57,419 --> 00:15:58,419
Should we go inside, then?

374
00:15:58,419 --> 00:15:59,325
PERFECT VISION

375
00:15:59,325 --> 00:16:00,149
Let's go.

376
00:16:00,149 --> 00:16:00,909
FWIP

377
00:16:00,909 --> 00:16:02,394
-Uh, is--
-Hush!

378
00:16:02,558 --> 00:16:03,558
Don't speak, don't turn around.

379
00:16:03,680 --> 00:16:05,132
No sudden moves,
stay low, stay frosty.

380
00:16:05,297 --> 00:16:06,584
[TANI] Frosty? What?

381
00:16:06,584 --> 00:16:08,068
[Suzuki whispering] Step inside
if you know what's good for you.

382
00:16:08,068 --> 00:16:09,068
[TANI] What's going on?

383
00:16:09,125 --> 00:16:10,313
[Yamada, Nishi
talking indistinctly]

384
00:16:11,797 --> 00:16:12,797
[SUZUKI] Why?!

385
00:16:12,797 --> 00:16:13,797
Why did he have to show up

386
00:16:13,843 --> 00:16:15,823
and burst my lovey-dovey
vacay bubble?

387
00:16:15,987 --> 00:16:17,407
-[TANI] Uh?
- Wait a minute!

388
00:16:17,571 --> 00:16:18,727
Are those two an official item?

389
00:16:18,891 --> 00:16:21,333
Or are they floating
in situationship limbo?

390
00:16:21,564 --> 00:16:22,851
Either way,
if they're on a date,

391
00:16:23,016 --> 00:16:24,797
things must be going
pretty well so far, eh?

392
00:16:24,963 --> 00:16:26,282
Smooth moves, Yamada.

393
00:16:26,448 --> 00:16:27,735
You got this, bud!

394
00:16:27,899 --> 00:16:30,110
I'm gonna explode when they
make the big announcement.

395
00:16:30,110 --> 00:16:31,110
[snickering]

396
00:16:31,199 --> 00:16:33,575
Don't you just love a clear,
sunny day?

397
00:16:33,740 --> 00:16:34,740
[TANI] Yeah.

398
00:16:34,941 --> 00:16:36,084
JUST RECENTLY
GLOMP

399
00:16:36,162 --> 00:16:37,414
Yo! Can you dig it?

400
00:16:37,414 --> 00:16:38,079
Uh, dig it?

401
00:16:38,079 --> 00:16:38,666
'Cause it's underground, get it?

402
00:16:38,666 --> 00:16:39,037
I guess so.

403
00:16:39,037 --> 00:16:40,037
[laughing excitedly]

404
00:16:40,568 --> 00:16:41,325
You know,

405
00:16:41,325 --> 00:16:41,851
date night next to the bay

406
00:16:41,851 --> 00:16:42,762
has a major
grown-up sort of aura,

407
00:16:42,762 --> 00:16:43,397
like we're super mature adults.

408
00:16:43,397 --> 00:16:44,200
[TANI] Admitting it
makes us sound like kids.

409
00:16:44,200 --> 00:16:44,788
It really does, though.

410
00:16:44,788 --> 00:16:45,669
I like to think
I've grown up a little bit.

411
00:16:45,669 --> 00:16:46,596
Yeah, but it's
lowkey embarrassing

412
00:16:46,596 --> 00:16:47,524
when a date is pulled
straight out of a chick flick.

413
00:16:47,524 --> 00:16:47,988
[TANI] Mm.

414
00:16:47,988 --> 00:16:48,988
[chuckles]

415
00:16:49,735 --> 00:16:50,708
[SUZUKI] I wonder
if Yamada and Nish

416
00:16:50,708 --> 00:16:51,249
will make it out here later.

417
00:16:51,249 --> 00:16:52,208
If he whisked her away
to a fancy spot like this,

418
00:16:52,208 --> 00:16:53,305
she'd melt into his arms
and be over the moon.

419
00:16:53,382 --> 00:16:54,382
OMG, they could totally
be on their way now.

420
00:16:54,404 --> 00:16:55,207
Eh, probs not.

421
00:16:55,207 --> 00:16:55,609
[TANI] Beautiful.

422
00:16:55,609 --> 00:16:56,609
Huh?

423
00:16:56,609 --> 00:16:59,370
-The view.
-Oh! Uh, yeah.

424
00:17:01,379 --> 00:17:02,760
If you want, Miyu,

425
00:17:02,970 --> 00:17:05,145
we could go over there
for a little while.

426
00:17:05,815 --> 00:17:07,656
[♪ sparkly music playing]

427
00:17:09,373 --> 00:17:11,673
[SUZUKI] Really?!

428
00:17:12,929 --> 00:17:16,152
Wow! This is peak existence!

429
00:17:16,361 --> 00:17:17,909
Nice skyline.

430
00:17:17,909 --> 00:17:20,169
I've always quietly hoped
I'd get to ride a Ferris wheel

431
00:17:20,378 --> 00:17:22,303
with someone
who's extra special to me.

432
00:17:22,512 --> 00:17:23,559
Quietly?

433
00:17:23,559 --> 00:17:25,734
-Loudly, very loudly.
-[laughs]

434
00:17:25,944 --> 00:17:27,032
-Of course it was.
-[chuckles]

435
00:17:27,241 --> 00:17:28,622
THAT GOT A LAUGH.

436
00:17:28,832 --> 00:17:31,175
When they turn girly
romance novels into movies,

437
00:17:31,384 --> 00:17:33,351
there's always
a cute Ferris wheel scene.

438
00:17:33,560 --> 00:17:34,648
[TANI]
Are they in the books, too?

439
00:17:34,857 --> 00:17:36,573
[laughs] I wouldn't know.

440
00:17:37,535 --> 00:17:39,754
Just me and the person I love,

441
00:17:39,963 --> 00:17:42,055
riding a Ferris wheel
alone together.

442
00:17:44,105 --> 00:17:46,240
Can I sit over by you?

443
00:17:46,449 --> 00:17:47,449
Huh?

444
00:17:54,285 --> 00:17:56,953
A moment straight
from my bucket list!

445
00:17:58,578 --> 00:17:59,662
STARE.

446
00:17:59,662 --> 00:18:01,830
[TANI] They are staring
right at us.

447
00:18:02,038 --> 00:18:04,748
[SUZUKI] They really oughta
tint these windows.

448
00:18:05,832 --> 00:18:07,875
Selfie time!

449
00:18:08,250 --> 00:18:09,291
[camera clicks]

450
00:18:10,542 --> 00:18:13,835
Ahh, what a fun-filled day!

451
00:18:14,252 --> 00:18:17,129
TBH, I wish
things got a bit mushier,

452
00:18:17,337 --> 00:18:20,171
but I didn't wanna
alert the PDA police.

453
00:18:21,338 --> 00:18:23,589
All the cool lights
got me so hyped!

454
00:18:23,798 --> 00:18:25,798
Christmas came early for us!

455
00:18:26,008 --> 00:18:27,091
[TANI] It really did.

456
00:18:27,299 --> 00:18:28,759
Speaking of Christmas,

457
00:18:28,759 --> 00:18:30,926
the best thing about it
is all the cozy, festive vibes

458
00:18:31,135 --> 00:18:32,886
leading up
to the actual holiday!

459
00:18:33,094 --> 00:18:34,761
The most wonderful time
of the year!

460
00:18:34,970 --> 00:18:37,049
♪ Jingle bells, jingle bells ♪

461
00:18:37,256 --> 00:18:38,916
[humming]

462
00:18:46,305 --> 00:18:47,840
For this Christmas,

463
00:18:48,048 --> 00:18:49,251
do you have any plans
in mind yet?

464
00:18:49,458 --> 00:18:50,538
Wha?!

465
00:18:50,745 --> 00:18:52,738
Uh, mm, mm...

466
00:18:52,945 --> 00:18:54,315
I'm not sure.

467
00:18:54,937 --> 00:18:59,046
I would be fine with anything
if it's with you.

468
00:19:01,039 --> 00:19:02,179
What about you, Yuusuke?

469
00:19:03,546 --> 00:19:04,546
Same here.

470
00:19:08,647 --> 00:19:09,647
[SUZUKI] It's so quiet.

471
00:19:10,328 --> 00:19:11,328
'Bout time.

472
00:19:11,526 --> 00:19:12,922
We finally got
a little bit of privacy.

473
00:19:22,269 --> 00:19:23,295
[car approaching]

474
00:19:23,750 --> 00:19:24,750
[both gasp]

475
00:19:24,750 --> 00:19:25,546
WHOOM

476
00:19:25,546 --> 00:19:26,116
STOPPED.

477
00:19:26,116 --> 00:19:27,997
[SUZUKI] Ugh, stupid car!

478
00:19:28,367 --> 00:19:29,421
Of course.

479
00:19:29,564 --> 00:19:30,564
[SUZUKI'S DAD]
Oh, look who it is!

480
00:19:30,564 --> 00:19:31,473
Hi, Miyu!

481
00:19:31,473 --> 00:19:32,243
Hi, Yuusuke!

482
00:19:32,243 --> 00:19:33,582
[SUZUKI] Dad?!

483
00:19:33,924 --> 00:19:35,862
No, we were so close!

484
00:19:36,004 --> 00:19:37,004
[SUZUKI'S MOM] When you said
you wouldn't need dinner,

485
00:19:37,004 --> 00:19:37,914
Dad and I took advantage

486
00:19:37,914 --> 00:19:38,914
and went on a little date
of our own.

487
00:19:38,914 --> 00:19:39,795
Hey, Yuusuke.

488
00:19:39,795 --> 00:19:40,963
Your house
is just over here, right?

489
00:19:40,963 --> 00:19:41,903
Yes, sir.

490
00:19:41,903 --> 00:19:43,043
Thank you for the ride.

491
00:19:43,585 --> 00:19:45,266
THUMP
THUMP

492
00:19:45,408 --> 00:19:46,408
[both groaning nervously]

493
00:19:47,147 --> 00:19:48,742
Wow, you two rode
the Ferris wheel?

494
00:19:48,885 --> 00:19:50,224
The view was absolutely gorge!

495
00:19:50,367 --> 00:19:51,450
A high-speed,
unhinged Ferris wheel

496
00:19:51,592 --> 00:19:52,592
would be a totally killer ride!

497
00:19:52,732 --> 00:19:54,186
Spill the tea, Suze.
What happened?

498
00:19:54,328 --> 00:19:55,354
Well, not to brag,

499
00:19:55,496 --> 00:19:56,551
but your girl's
living the rom-com dream

500
00:19:56,693 --> 00:19:57,693
with extra rom.

501
00:19:57,719 --> 00:19:59,486
[HONDA] Aww,
that pin looks cute on you.

502
00:19:59,629 --> 00:20:00,629
[gasps] Yeah?

503
00:20:00,659 --> 00:20:01,659
Thank you, Hon.

504
00:20:29,839 --> 00:20:30,839
So...

505
00:20:31,042 --> 00:20:33,280
Did you and Yamada
have a good time?

506
00:20:33,284 --> 00:20:34,284
[whimpers]

507
00:20:34,338 --> 00:20:36,089
What? You went to Chinatown?

508
00:20:36,292 --> 00:20:37,513
-That's rad.
-Yeah.

509
00:20:37,839 --> 00:20:39,752
Convenience store steamies
can't compare.

510
00:20:39,955 --> 00:20:42,641
[TANI] Huh. Yamada went
to Chinatown, too.

511
00:20:42,845 --> 00:20:44,432
[TAIRA] Who did he go with?

512
00:20:44,636 --> 00:20:46,874
No, stay nonchalant.
Don't engage.

513
00:20:48,421 --> 00:20:50,008
[SUZUKI] Ooh!

514
00:20:50,211 --> 00:20:52,735
It's already starting
to get dark out so early,

515
00:20:53,590 --> 00:20:54,590
[chuckles]

516
00:20:54,729 --> 00:20:56,398
You've got ice cube fingies.

517
00:20:56,601 --> 00:20:58,025
Yours are hot.

518
00:20:58,230 --> 00:21:00,550
How are you so warm, Miyu?

519
00:21:00,757 --> 00:21:01,881
[gasps]

520
00:21:01,881 --> 00:21:04,254
-Yuusuke, Yuusuke, lookie here!
-Hmm?

521
00:21:04,670 --> 00:21:06,544
[SUZUKI] They added the "warm
and cozy" winter drinks

522
00:21:06,751 --> 00:21:08,334
to the vending machine.

523
00:21:08,334 --> 00:21:09,124
COCOA WITH CREAM - CORN POTAGE
CONSOMME SOUP - BEEF FLAVOR

524
00:21:09,124 --> 00:21:10,665
Huzzah!

525
00:21:10,665 --> 00:21:12,580
When the vending machines say
the seasons are changing,

526
00:21:12,788 --> 00:21:13,870
then it's real.

527
00:21:13,870 --> 00:21:14,990
You look forward
to this every year?

528
00:21:15,720 --> 00:21:18,682
-Oh, you can snow bank on it.
-[laughs]

529
00:21:18,896 --> 00:21:20,527
You gotta shake 'em vigorously

530
00:21:20,743 --> 00:21:22,159
like a chemistry project
for your mouth

531
00:21:22,374 --> 00:21:23,374
you don't wanna fail!

532
00:21:23,576 --> 00:21:25,250
Looks intense.

533
00:21:26,967 --> 00:21:29,972
[SUZUKI] Just like I cherish
the changing of the seasons,

534
00:21:30,187 --> 00:21:33,321
I wanna cherish the little
changes between us, too.

535
00:21:34,866 --> 00:21:37,228
Could you, uh, stick to "Miyu"?

536
00:21:37,656 --> 00:21:39,803
I like it when you're
more casual with me.

537
00:21:40,018 --> 00:21:41,018
[TANI] Hmm?

538
00:21:42,937 --> 00:21:44,010
-[Suzuki giggles]

539
00:21:44,224 --> 00:21:46,800
SO IT DIDN'T SEEM CASUAL
AFTER ALL.

540
00:21:47,016 --> 00:21:48,775
[TANI] So, you like Miyu better?

541
00:21:48,990 --> 00:21:51,137
[SUZUKI] Uh-huh.
When I hear Miyu,

542
00:21:51,480 --> 00:21:54,442
it means Yuusuke's
all cute and embarrassed.

543
00:21:57,619 --> 00:21:58,619
Mm.

544
00:21:58,990 --> 00:22:00,344
That's a messed-up reason.

545
00:22:00,513 --> 00:22:02,002
[laughs]

546
00:22:02,171 --> 00:22:03,491
Miyu.

547
00:22:03,491 --> 00:22:06,029
[Suzuki giggling] Hey, he's not
as embarrassed as before.

548
00:22:06,198 --> 00:22:08,160
Little by little,
things are changing.

549
00:22:08,160 --> 00:22:09,141
SQUIGGLE

550
00:22:09,141 --> 00:22:09,987
[laughs]

551
00:22:09,987 --> 00:22:12,322
[laughing]

552
00:22:14,826 --> 00:22:15,942
[SUZUKI] I'm doing it.

553
00:22:17,499 --> 00:22:19,157
I'm bringing the poles together.

554
00:22:19,326 --> 00:22:20,326
Wait, you're what?

555
00:22:20,375 --> 00:22:21,966
HEH HEH.

556
00:22:22,134 --> 00:22:23,759
[♪ closing theme song playing]
